        • [ - ] Mquaak - member since 27-Aug-12

          Ligeon replaced Ricardo van Rhijn at RB with Ajax. van Rhijn was suspended due to his red card last week. While van Rhijn has not been displaying his best efforts last months, questions were asked why coach Frank de Boer kept playing van Rhijn instead of Ligeon. This match showed De Boer might think of replacing van Rhijn for the next matches to give Ligeon a run of matches. His 8 crosses showed he has the skills to provide forward runs. On the other hand Ligeon was not tested as Feyenoord did not play their normal 4-3-3. For this match they switched back to 4-4-2 which meant Ligeon had no direct opponent to play against. When running forward Feyenoord’s young star Vilhena was forced to choose between taking over Schöne or picking up Ligeon. Ajax took advantage of his doubts and scored the 2-1 while a cross from Ligeon reached Sigthorsson who scored a beautiful header.
